Basenji - a portable volume indexer
http://launchpad.net/basenji


GNU/LINUX/GNOME:
================

Requirements:

	mono (2.4 or later)
	glib-sharp (2.12.9 or later)
	gtk-sharp (2.12.9 or later)
	gnome-sharp (2.24.1 or later)
	gnome-vfs-sharp (2.24.1 or later)
	ndesk-dbus (0.6 or later)
	ndesk-dbus-glib (0.4.1 or later)
	mono-cairo (2.4.2.3 or later)
	libextractor1c2a (0.5.21 or later)
    libextractor-plugins (0.5.21 or later)
    
Compile:

	./configure (non-gnome: ./configure --config=RELEASE)
	make
	make install

	NOTE:
	if you get a "GLib.GException: Couldn't recognize the image file format for file 'data/basenji.svg'" runtime error,
	you most likely don't have SVG pixbuf loaders installed (package librsvg2-common in ubuntu).
	

MS Windows:
===========

Requirements:

	.NET 3.5 Framework
	Gtk# for .NET (http://www.go-mono.com/mono-downloads/download.html)
	System.Data.SQLite (http://sqlite.phxsoftware.com/)
	libextractor (http://www.gnu.org/software/libextractor/download.html)
	
Compile:

	Open Basenji_win32.sln in Visual Studio 2008.
